<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="567" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Etymology.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves &amp; Viegas, 2022" authorityName="Gonçalves &amp; Viegas" authorityYear="2022" box="[394,592,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Rosalydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavieri" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[394,592,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Rosalydia xavieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[600,776,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[600,648,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">gen.</emphasis>
et 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[685,776,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a tribute to the collector Francisco Felipe Xavier Filho, affectionately known as “Chiquinho”, an expert collector of neotropical insects, mainly from the Brazilian Amazonian entomofauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="567" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the known species for the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves &amp; Viegas, 2022" authorityName="Gonçalves &amp; Viegas" authorityYear="2022" box="[771,967,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Rosalydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="567" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xavieri" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[771,967,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Rosalydia xavieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[972,1139,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[972,1020,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">gen.</emphasis>
et 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1051,1139,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the most differentiated characteristics of the male terminalia: the caudal process of the pygofer is short, not exceeding the ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,181,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1436,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Rosalydia inpa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 16, head, frontal view; 17, forewing; 18, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 19, process of pygofer, caudal view; 20, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 21, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 22, connective and style, dorsal view; 23, style, lateral view; 24, aedeagus, lateral view; 25, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 16 = 1.0 mm, 17 = 2.0 mm, 18–25 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5964498/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); the subgenital plates have the inner margin with teeth increasing in size towards apex (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1332,834,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–25" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,181,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1436,181,1785]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–25. Rosalydia inpa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 16, head, frontal view; 17, forewing; 18, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 19, process of pygofer, caudal view; 20, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 21, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 22, connective and style, dorsal view; 23, style, lateral view; 24, aedeagus, lateral view; 25, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 16 = 1.0 mm, 17 = 2.0 mm, 18–25 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5964498/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); and the aedeagus has a pair of expansions in the basal third (
<figureCitation box="[739,871,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–36" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[155,1424,189,1789]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1795]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 26–36. Rosalydia xavieri gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 26, head, frontal view; 27, forewing; 28, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 29, process of pygofer, caudal view; 30, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 31, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 32, connective and style, dorsal view; 33, style, lateral view; 34, aedeagus, lateral view; 35, aedeagus, caudal view; 36, aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 26 = 1.0 mm, 27 = 2.0 mm, 28–36 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5964500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5964500/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="567">Figs 28–30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
